verbose_text: Transfection of the cells with 3 different siRNAs against Tb4 (siRNA-1, -2 and -3) significantly decreased the mRNA expression levels of Tb4 by approximately 70-90% compared to those in the untreated control mDE6 cells (Ut) and the mDE6 cells treated with a universal negative control siRNA (Cont) (XREF_FIG).
